On September 30, 2021, the President signed into law the "Extending Government Funding and Delivering Emergency Assistance Act" (H.R. 5305). This law includes a short-term continuing resolution that provides fiscal year 2022 appropriations to Federal agencies until December 3, 2021, allowing them to continue their projects and activities. The law also includes supplemental appropriations for disaster relief and Afghanistan evacuees. Additionally, it extends several expiring authorizations. The President expressed gratitude to Chairman Patrick Leahy, Vice Chairman Richard Shelby, Chair Rosa DeLauro, and Ranking Member Kay Granger for their leadership in this matter.